==English==

===Etymology===
A calque of Chinese [[丢脸]] (simplified) / [[丟臉]] (traditional) / [[diū liǎn]] (pinyin), literally meaning "being unable to show one's face in public".

===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=to [[lose]] [[face]]|loses face|losing face|lost face}}

# {{idiom}} To lose the respect of others, to be humiliated or experience public disgrace.

